task.summary: Default task
Set up project
Classes are all outlined with most basic instance variables and methods, constructors, and getters. First test cases were created and passed.
Added HashMaps for room names (String) to rooms (Room objects) in Layout, and direction name (String) to room (String) in Layout and Room, respectively, to make getting necessary information easier.
Realized hashmaps weren't loading correctly b/c Gson doesn't call constructor when creating objects, added loadHashmap() helpers (and tested more)
Added javadoc comments for Room, Layout, and Direction classes
added some more tests, almost finished with interactive GUI
Fixed a couple bugs, allowed game to quit and end when reached destination
Added some comments
fixed another bug with directions formatting
Added functionality to instantiate Layout object from URL, testing for that, equals testing for all classes
Program now prompts user to either opt for default siebel JSON or enter in their own URL to a layout JSON. Added more specific error messages.
Fixed some bugs with ignoring capitalization of direction names, printing final destination.
Added functionality to allow testing of valid layouts (can reach end), testing for that method, added empty string handling for url exceptions.
Separate main method from PlayAdventure class, added more testing for getting Layout from URL.
Add support for command line arguments, ability to read Layout json from filepath, testing
Update DEVELOPMENT.md
Add items to Room class, Player class, ability to pick up and drop items, update DEVELOPMENT.md
Fix markdown?
Fix Markdown
Start basic dealing functions for Clue, add tests for them
Add javadoc comments for Player and Clue classes
Add turn taking capability
Complete basic functionality, some bug fixes needed
